<br>
--Sky Isle 7 (not to mention issues making pets unusable on quite a few spots/times elsewhere)<br>
--Hate (I dont care what some folk say I have used pets there and bar about 3 spots its INSANE what can happen with pets)<br>
--City of Mist needs some dern careful work in some spots.<br>
--Hole, oh my gawd dont DARE tell me you can use pets safely in most of the hole cause you CAN'T, ugh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Several areas they are cool, but near buildings, forget it.<br>
--Chardok, still has bad pathing deeper but most upper is cool I don't know if the loony warping into walls still happens though in &quot;new&quot; chardok<br>
--Crushbone, yes simple crushbone, ugh. Go walk a pet round there, sheesh.<br>
--Kedge keep, yeah can use pets but you gotta keep yer eye on the pet like a hawk.<br>
--HS has a couple of weird kinks in pathing you have to be aware of, but real consideration is with aggro (/pet hold should be a lvl 51 skill)<br>
--Najeena, ever met your pet coming BACK the way? :&gt; pets TP in there to zoneline<br>
--ToV, pets? aye right!!! (can be done with /pet hold or EXTREMELY careful use but no, not worth it normally)<br>
--Fear, several AOE mobs, I've used pets a lot there but its TRICKY as heck, again /pet hold should be easier to get.<br>
--Other places have issues o but you get my poiint.<br>
<br>
For various reasons I'd say you can only use pets in most raids about 50% if that, which SUCKS.<br>
<br>
What mages should learn:<br>
1) WAIT! WAIT! WAIT!! wait for mobs to be engaged and mezzed, THEN send pet in when it looks good and no pull is inc.<br>
2)  learn to position self and pet so less chance of aggro, i.e. behind everyone else and away from pathing.<br>
3) Check pathing of area, when in doubt do NOT have a pet up or at least do not use it till sure.<br>
4) have Earthen Boots hot keyed, if not, bugger off, you shoudln't be in any higher lvl setting without them<br>
5) When working with a chanter you will have to learn to anticpiate his mezzes and they should know to STUN a mob your pet is on, THEN mez. By anticipating mezzes, checking to see enchanter casting spell messages, you can better time /pet back off if needed.<br>
6) Debuffing is IMPORTANT, especially on tougher mobs or in caster heavy situations, this includes xp and raid situations. For example using Malosini etc on a krup or Illis frogs greatly helps everyone.<br>
7) Dont flipping over nuke, thats for dumb wizzies, and they at least have skins buffs to stop them getting dinked :&gt;<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Pet mezz is good, too few groups realize that but its something you have to use with care.<br>
9) if it seesm your pet is wandering off, quickly spind round to chekc it isnt ghosting, if it isnt  kill pet isntantly.<br>
10) Pet get lost and invis are NOT GOOD enough to kill pet,  despite what some, ahem, folk, think. See (4)<br>
11) If pet disappears quickly hit earth boots.<br>
12) If strange aggro occurs, hit earthen boots.<br>
13) Don't walk pets to spots unless it really IS safe, reclaim pet and resummon. Do not use /pet sit and Summon Companion if there is danger of resapwn where pet is.<br>
<br>
*gets of soap box* <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
Archmage<br>
