<br>
Mages need work in implementation, not in design.  Think about it, if pathing wern't an issue, would mages be &quot;broken&quot; when their pets could be used in all zones without fear of pathing causing problems?  Sure, in the 50+ range, they need a TUNE-UP, no question, but they arn't broken, the implementation is.<br>
<br>
Wizards are an example of a class where most things work as designed, but it's clear that the design is the limiting factor and that's where wizards need to be worked on.  Having damage scale properly from level 1 to 60, instead of these huge jumps in damage here and there would help wizards with the design issues.  Putting the focus items into the game so that wizard-only items help wizards in DD spells more than other classes.<br>
