<br>
Instead of a Magic based DD spell, Magicians have a fast casting pet. This pet will poof when the target dies. It is not a DD spell like a Lure, but it will be a cheap casting pet that will poof after the MoB dies. No more pathing problems because you have to cast it in melee range. <br>
<br>
make it a high dmg hitter and it will die faster due to aggro.<br>
make it have a duration like eye of zomm and it will poof after awhile<br>
<br>
But all this combined will result in fast dmg over a short period of time. DMG is melee based so it is like a Lure spell and making it poof after a short time or when the MoB is dead makes it a one time only spell like a DD.<br>
<br>
The Mentioned Ball of stone would be an earth elemental type spell with a big pickaxe Piercing away for 200 each pierce.<br>
<br>
The Ball of Iron would be a big fire elemental with a Huge sword slashing for 200.<br>
<br>
The Ball of Ice would be a water elemental with a big club blunting for 200.<br>
<br>
The Ball of glass would be a air elemental with punches for 200.<br>
<br>
No spells do they cast, they just Hit a few times for alot of dmg. the MoB AC prevents high dmg and the duration prevents overkills. <p><center><img src="http://httpd.chello.nl/j.wensveen1/images/Branaman.jpg" width="400" alt="" border="0" align="center"><br><table><tr>
